commentary: Mohammed Shami to Shamsur Rahman, OUT it's over for Shamsur! The short ball brings a wicket, but not before Rayudu and Shami end up making a complete hash of it. It was a surprise short ball and Shamsur tried to whip it to the leg side, but he got a thick leading edge that ballooned to the off side, towards cover, not very far from the pitch. Shami charged, and Rayudu charged towards the ball too, without anyone calling for it. Shami takes it in the end, but that was just about to go down..Shami's hand actually hit Rayudu's face there

commentary: Mohammed Shami to Mushfiqur Rahim, OUT Mushy's fine innings comes to an end! He slaps a high full toss straight to deep midwicket, but the umpire wants to check it for a) front-fott, and b) the height. First one is fine, and second one should be fine too as Mushy had charged way down the pitch. It looks like it was waist high when he made contact, but the ball had another two meters to go to the stumps. That's it, the umpires think it was fine. A wonderful innings from Mushy comes to an end. The Indian fielders pat him on the back..

commentary: Rubel Hossain to Rahane, no run he has slapped that short of length delivery straight to midwicket! or is it! Mominul, the catcher, is not very sure. The umpires are going to check that. The catch was taken cleanly - that's what the replays show - but the doubtful part is after that. Was he able to keep his fingers underneath as he hit the ground? Slight wobble of his hands as he has the first grab at the ball - it's right on the edge of his fingers as he comes up .. Not out is the verdict.. So the umpire reckons the ball might have touched the ground

Slight wobble of his hands as he has the first grab at the ball - it's right on the edge of his fingers as he comes up .. Not out is the verdict.. So the umpire reckons the ball might have touched the ground
